text.tspan: 1 and 2 are the same. They are just counting the 5 input bits (mod 4).
3 is the same as 1 and 2 for the first half, but 1 less for the rest. This is also just a simple
counter of the 4 input bits and the difference is due to the 2 p's.
4 and 5 are the same. The second half is just 1+ the first half.
n is the parity of the first 5
p is the parity of the first 9. (the parity of the next 4 plus the parity of the first 5)
r is the parity of all 12 and therefore is the LSB of the output
q is the MSB of the count+p (mod 4)
t is q xor m, s is overflow of a-e
if m==0 s= atleast2 of abc
v = t xor o = m xor o xor q
the 2s place bit of the sum of all the inputs
